3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper applies worst-case and average-case analyses to the new data structures. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper deals with finding the closest-pair in a range of points, which involves numerical computations. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the range closest-pair problem finds applications in computer graphics and image processing.
